{"title_page": "Erik Pettersson (cyclist)", "text_new": "{{short description|Swedish cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Erik Pettersson\n| image          = Erik Pettersson (cyclist).jpg\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1944|4|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[V\u00e5rg\u00e5rda]], Sweden\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|180|cm|ftin|abbr=on}} \n| weight         = {{convert|67|kg|abbr=on}}\n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = \n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = 1963\u20131969\n| amateurteam1   =  V\u00e5rg\u00e5rda CK\n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{flag|SWE}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[1968 Summer Olympics|1968 Mexico City]] | [[Cycling at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team time trial|Team time trial]] }}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1964 Summer Olympics|1964 Tokyo]] | [[Cycling at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team time trial|Team time trial]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UCI Road World Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold |[[1967 UCI Road World Championships|1967 Heerlen]]|Team time trial}}\n{{MedalGold |[[1968 UCI Road World Championships|1968 Imola]]|Team time trial}}\n{{MedalGold |[[1969 UCI Road World Championships|1969 Zolder]]|Team time trial}}\n| show-medals = yes\n}}\n[[File:Faglumbroderna.jpg|thumb|The F\u00e5glum brothers 1967. Erik is second from the left.]]\n'''Erik H\u00e5kan Pettersson''' (born 4 April 1944) is a retired Swedish cyclist. He was part of the road racing team of four Pettersson brothers, known as [[F\u00e5glum brothers]], who won the world title in 1967\u20131969 and a silver medal at the 1968 Olympics; three of the brothers were also part of the bronze-winning road team at the 1964 Games. In 1967 they were awarded the [[Svenska Dagbladet Gold Medal]].<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pe/erik-pettersson-1.html |title=Erik Pettersson Olympic Results |accessdate=18 August 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\nErik was the fastest sprinter among the F\u00e5glum brothers; he was nicknamed R\u00f6dtoppen for his red hair. he turned professional after the 1969 World Championships, together with the other brothers, but had little success and retired in 1971.<ref name=sok>[http://sok.se/idrottare/idrottare/e/erik-faglum.html Erik F\u00e5glum]. Swedish Olympic Committee</ref><ref name=ca>[http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=3703 Erik Pettersson]. cyclingarchives.com</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Erik Pettersson (cyclist)}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pettersson, Erik}}\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swedish male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Sweden]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Sweden]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Sweden]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in cycling]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1968 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1968 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:UCI Road World Champions (elite men)]]\n[[Category:F\u00e5glum brothers]]\n\n{{Sweden-cycling-bio-stub}}\n{{Sweden-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Swedish cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Erik Pettersson\n| image          = Erik Pettersson (cyclist).jpg\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1944|4|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[V\u00e5rg\u00e5rda]], Sweden\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|180|cm|ftin|abbr=on}} \n| weight         = {{convert|67|kg|abbr=on}}\n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = \n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = 1963\u20131969\n| amateurteam1   =  V\u00e5rg\u00e5rda CK\n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{flag|SWE}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[1968 Summer Olympics|1968 Mexico City]] | [[Cycling at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team time trial|Team time trial]] }}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1964 Summer Olympics|1964 Tokyo]] | [[Cycling at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team time trial|Team time trial]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UCI Road World Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold |[[1967 UCI Road World Championships|1967 Heerlen]]|Team time trial}}\n{{MedalGold |[[1968 UCI Road World Championships|1968 Imola]]|Team time trial}}\n{{MedalGold |[[1969 UCI Road World Championships|1969 Zolder]]|Team time trial}}\n| show-medals = yes\n}}\n[[File:Faglumbroderna.jpg|thumb|The F\u00e5glum brothers 1967. Erik is second from the left.]]\n'''Erik H\u00e5kan Pettersson''' (born 4 April 1944) is a retired Swedish cyclist. He was part of the road racing team of four Pettersson brothers, known as [[F\u00e5glum brothers]], who won the world title in 1967\u20131969 and a silver medal at the 1968 Olympics; three of the brothers were also part of the bronze-winning road team at the 1964 Games. In 1967 they were awarded the [[Svenska Dagbladet Gold Medal]].<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pe/erik-pettersson-1.html |title=Erik Pettersson Olympic Results |accessdate=18 August 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\nErik was the fastest sprinter among the F\u00e5glum brothers; he was nicknamed R\u00f6dtoppen for his red hair. he turned professional after the 1969 World Championships, together with the other brothers, but had little success and retired in 1971.<ref name=sok>[http://sok.se/idrottare/idrottare/e/erik-faglum.html Erik F\u00e5glum]. Swedish Olympic Committee</ref><ref name=ca>[http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=3703 Erik Pettersson]. cyclingarchives.com</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Erik Pettersson (cyclist)}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pettersson, Erik}}\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swedish male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Sweden]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Sweden]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Sweden]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in cycling]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1968 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1968 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:UCI Road World Champions (elite men)]]\n[[Category:F\u00e5glum brothers]]\n\n{{Sweden-cycling-bio-stub}}\n{{Sweden-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erik_Pettersson_(cyclist)"}
